Johannesburg – The department of health said that 12 267 new Covid-19 cases were recorded in the past 24 hours. The cumulative amount of cases in the country now stands at 1 337 926. The department of health further said, “Regrettably, we report a further 254 deaths. Our recoveries now stand at 1 098 441 representing a recovery rate of 82,1%.” The president said during his last address to the nation that the country recorded more than 190 000 new covid-19 infections and more than 4600 deaths this year, forcing him to keep the country on an adjusted level 3 lockdown.  